     {q:"Why are rational functions useful for modelling certain real-world situations, like rates?", options:["They can represent relationships involving division, such as rates that change based on other values","Rational functions can never model real-world situations","These functions only apply to whole numbers, not real-world rates","This type of function has no practical use"], answer:0}
