     {q:"Which factor might limit a population’s growth and contribute to its carrying capacity?", options:["A factor with no connection to the environment","A factor entirely unrelated to survival needs","Availability of food and resources","The colour of the organisms in the population"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why might a population decline if it exceeds its environment’s carrying capacity?", options:["Resources may become insufficient to support all individuals in the population","Populations can grow indefinitely with no environmental limits","Exceeding carrying capacity always has no effect on a population","This concept has no connection to resource availability"], answer:0},
     {q:"Why is understanding carrying capacity important for wildlife management and conservation?", options:["It helps guide decisions to maintain sustainable population levels in an ecosystem","Wildlife management never considers population size","This concept has no relevance to conservation efforts","Carrying capacity has no connection to ecosystem health"], answer:0}
