     {q:"Why do readers often find bildungsroman novels relatable?", options:["Coming-of-age stories never explore identity or self-discovery","They reflect universal experiences of growing up, identity, and self-discovery","This type of novel has no connection to readers’ own experiences","A reason unrelated to reading comprehension"], answer:1},
     {q:"Which of these would best signal a turning point in a bildungsroman?", options:["A concept unrelated to this type of novel","A significant challenge that changes how the protagonist sees themselves or the world","A moment with no impact on the protagonist at all","An event that occurs with no connection to the plot"], answer:1}
